### 1.2 — Fix refresh token hashing inconsistency (S3)

**Severity:** Critical | **Effort:** 30 min

#### [MODIFY] [auth.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/auth.routes.ts)

**Problem:** Login (line ~195) stores the **raw** refresh token in the DB. The `/refresh` endpoint (line ~287) stores a **hashed** version. Token comparison in `/refresh` uses `findFirst` searching for raw token, but on rotation stores hashed — mismatch.

**Fix:**
- Hash refresh token before storing in ALL locations (register, login, Google OAuth, Facebook OAuth)
- On `/refresh`, hash the incoming token before DB lookup
- Ensure `findFirst` query compares hashed values consistently

**Files changed:**
- [auth.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/auth.routes.ts) — 4 locations where refresh tokens are stored

#### Verification
- Extend existing [auth.middleware.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/tests/auth.middleware.test.ts) with a new `describe('Refresh Token Hashing')` block:
  - Test that stored tokens are never raw
  - Test that refresh flow correctly matches hashed tokens
```bash
cd c:\Users\MahmoodCenter\Desktop\news-platform-next\server
npx vitest run src/tests/auth.middleware.test.ts
```

