### 1.3 — Prevent User cascade delete destroying articles (B3)

**Severity:** Critical | **Effort:** 20 min

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/prisma/schema.prisma)

**Problem:** `Article.author` relation uses `onDelete: Cascade` (line 93) — deleting a user permanently destroys ALL their articles.

**Fix:**
- Change `onDelete: Cascade` to `onDelete: Restrict` on the Article→User relation
- This means a user cannot be deleted if they have articles — admin must reassign articles first
- Add a `deletedAt DateTime?` field to `User` for soft-delete (groundwork for D1)
- Update [user.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/user.routes.ts) DELETE endpoint to soft-delete (set `isActive: false, deletedAt: now()`) instead of hard delete

**Files changed:**
- [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/prisma/schema.prisma) — Article relation + User model
- [user.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/user.routes.ts) — DELETE /api/users/:id endpoint

#### Verification
```bash
cd c:\Users\MahmoodCenter\Desktop\news-platform-next\server
npx prisma migrate dev --name prevent-user-cascade-delete
npx vitest run
```
- Manual: Attempt to delete a user who has articles → should receive error message saying "Cannot delete user with existing articles"

