### 1.4 — Add HTML sanitization for article content (S6)

**Severity:** High | **Effort:** 30 min

#### [MODIFY] [article.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/article.routes.ts)

**Problem:** Article `content` field accepts raw HTML with no sanitization — stored XSS is possible.

**Fix:**
- Install `dompurify` and `jsdom` (jsdom already installed)
- Create a `sanitizeHtml()` utility in `server/src/services/` or `server/src/utils/`
- Call it on `content` in both POST and PATCH article routes
- Allowlist: standard HTML tags (p, h1-h6, a, img, ul, ol, li, strong, em, blockquote, br, div, span, table, etc.)
- Strip: script, iframe, onX event attributes, javascript: URLs

#### [NEW] `server/src/utils/sanitize.ts`
- Export `sanitizeHtml(html: string): string`
- Export `sanitizeText(text: string): string` for plain-text fields (title, excerpt)

#### Verification
- Write a new test file `server/src/tests/sanitize.test.ts`:
  - Test XSS vectors are stripped: `<script>alert('xss')</script>`, `<img onerror="alert(1)">`, `javascript:` URLs
  - Test valid HTML is preserved: `<p>`, `<strong>`, `<a href="https://...">`, `<img src="...">`
```bash
cd c:\Users\MahmoodCenter\Desktop\news-platform-next\server
npx vitest run src/tests/sanitize.test.ts
```

