### 1.5 — Move JWT tokens from localStorage to httpOnly cookies (S1)

**Severity:** Critical | **Effort:** 2-3 hours

> [!WARNING]
> This is the largest change in Sprint 1. It requires coordinated frontend + backend changes.

#### [MODIFY] [auth.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/auth.routes.ts)

- Set JWT access token as `httpOnly`, `Secure`, `SameSite=Strict` cookie on login/register/refresh/OAuth responses
- Set refresh token as a separate `httpOnly` cookie with a longer `maxAge`
- Remove token from JSON response body (keep only user data)
- Read tokens from cookies in `/refresh` and `/logout`

#### [MODIFY] [auth.ts (middleware)](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/middleware/auth.ts)

- Read JWT from cookies instead of / in addition to `Authorization` header
- Install `cookie-parser` middleware

#### [MODIFY] [app.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/app.ts)

- Add `cookie-parser` middleware
- Update CORS to include `credentials: true` (already set)

#### [MODIFY] [api.ts (frontend)](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/src/services/api.ts)

- Remove localStorage token reads/writes
- Set `withCredentials: true` on axios instance
- Remove `Authorization` header from request interceptor (cookies are sent automatically)
- Update token refresh logic to use cookie-based flow

#### [MODIFY] [AuthContext](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx)

- Remove localStorage token management
- Auth state derived from `/api/auth/me` call result
- Login/logout trigger cookie-based endpoints

#### Verification
- Update existing [auth.middleware.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/tests/auth.middleware.test.ts) to test cookie-based auth
- Update [article.publish.integration.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/tests/article.publish.integration.test.ts) if header-based auth changes
```bash
