### 2.2 — Add transaction to article creation (B2)

**Severity:** High | **Effort:** 30 min

#### [MODIFY] [article.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/article.routes.ts)

**Problem:** Article + tags + activity log are created in separate queries — partial failure leaves orphaned data.

**Fix:** Wrap the create flow in `prisma.$transaction()`:
```typescript
const result = await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
    const article = await tx.article.create({ ... });
    if (tags?.length) await tx.articleTag.createMany({ ... });
    await tx.activityLog.create({ ... });
    return article;
});
```

#### Verification
- Existing [article.publish.integration.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/tests/article.publish.integration.test.ts) covers the create flow — run it to ensure no regression
```bash
cd c:\Users\MahmoodCenter\Desktop\news-platform-next\server
npx vitest run src/tests/article.publish.integration.test.ts
```

---

### 2.3 — Fix slug generation race condition (B1)

**Severity:** High | **Effort:** 20 min

#### [MODIFY] [article.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/article.routes.ts)

**Fix:** Use a `try/catch` around `prisma.article.create()` — if unique constraint violation on `slug`, append a random suffix and retry (up to 3 times). This is more reliable than the current check-then-create pattern.

#### Verification
- Manual: Create two articles with the same title simultaneously — both should succeed with different slugs

