## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Sprint 1.5 (JWT cookies)** is the highest-risk change — it touches auth flow across both frontend and backend. Please confirm:
> 1. Are there any mobile apps or external API consumers that rely on the current `Authorization: Bearer` header pattern? If so, we need to support both cookies and headers.
> 2. Is the backend deployed with HTTPS in production? (`Secure` cookies require HTTPS)
> 3. Should we start with Sprint 1 (security) or would you prefer a different order?
